          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1610626820734-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1610626820734-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, drain your <strong>jumbo prawns</strong>, then add them to the pan and cook for 2-3 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/28-04-22_11h19m42s-APIC-1653322704598-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/28-04-22_11h19m42s-APIC-1653322704598-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/28-04-22_11h19m42s-APIC-1653322704598-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/28-04-22_11h19m42s-APIC-1653322704598-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/28-04-22_11h19m42s-APIC-1653322704598-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail and chop your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> into small, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped courgette</strong> and <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min further until the courgette has started to soften</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/28-04-22_11h23m37s-APIC-1653322785021-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/28-04-22_11h23m37s-APIC-1653322785021-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/28-04-22_11h23m37s-APIC-1653322785021-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/28-04-22_11h23m37s-APIC-1653322785021-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/28-04-22_11h23m37s-APIC-1653322785021-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the courgette softens, chop your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the<strong> chopped creamed coconut</strong>, <strong>Thai green curry paste </strong>and a pinch of<strong> sugar</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong> and your<strong> lime leaf[ves] </strong>– this is your<strong> Thai green curry stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1589292966629-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1589292966629-x400.jpg",
